Cape Town City midfielder Mpho Makola has reaffirmed his commitment to the Premier Soccer League club by signing a contract extension. The 34-year-old joined the Citizens from Orlando Pirates in 2019 and has gone on to become an important player for the club. A former ASD Cape Town player, Makola has also played for Free State Stars. A short statement from the club's official Twitter account read: "Cape Town City have confirmed a decision on the future of former Orlando Pirates midfielder Mpho Makola. "Makola will remain with the Cape Town-based outfit until June 2021, after signing a new one-year deal on the weekend."Makola has played 19 Absa Premiership games this season, scoring once and creating one goal. 